---
import Banner from "../components/Banner.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Ideas — Mediainc"
  description="JACH, Media Inc's research and authorship division: writing and visual work that examines how meaning, behavior and economic value are formed in contemporary culture."
>
    <div class="bg-white">
        <Banner image="/images/jach/L_Media63 (1).jpg" />
    </div>
    <section
        class="flex flex-col justify-center font-medium font-['EB_Garamond'] text-center my-10"
    >
        <img
            src="/images/jach/JACH-w.png"
            alt="JACH"
            class="h-6 w-auto object-contain mb-8"
        />

        <section class="flex flex-col gap-5 my-1">
            <h1 class="text-[65px] leading-[1] font-bold text-center">
                Where meaning and value are explored through ideas.
            </h1>

            <p class="text-[30px] leading-[1]">
                Media Inc operates on a defined point of view: value is not
                inherent. It is constructed through perception, context, and
                narrative. This perspective is developed through JACH, the
                company's research and authorship division — an ongoing body of
                writing and visual work that examines how meaning, behavior, and
                economic value are formed in contemporary culture.
            </p>
        </section>

        <div class="py-8 text-[30px] leading-[1]">
            <h3 class="font-bold">Core Themes</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The Psychology of Money and Wealth</li>
                <li>The Semantics of our Cultural Identity</li>
                <li>Idiosyncrasy of Luck and Will</li>
                <li>The Democratization of Pleasure</li>
                <li>Media Gone Wrong: an Industry in Crisis</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="flex justify-center gap-6 mt-10">
                <img
                    src="/images/jach/L_Media63.jpg"
                    alt="JACH research piece"
                    class="w-auto h-60 object-cover"
                />
                <img
                    src="/images/jach/L_Media67-400x400.jpg"
                    alt="JACH research piece"
                    class="w-auto h-60 object-cover"
                />
                <img
                    src="/images/jach/L_Media45-300x372.jpg"
                    alt="JACH research piece"
                    class="w-auto h-60 object-cover"
                />
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="text-[30px] leading-[1]">
            <h3 class="font-bold my-5">Visual Work</h3>
            <p class="text-[65px] leading-[1] font-bold">
                A selection of visual pieces accompanies this research — not as
                illustration, but as a parallel form of inquiry into perception,
                meaning, and cultural tension.
            </p>
        </div>

        <section
            class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center text-[27px] leading-[1.15] mb-10"
        >
            <div class="flex justify-center gap-6 my-5">
                <img
                    src="/images/jach/7.jpg"
                    alt="JACH visual work"
                    class="w-auto h-60 object-cover"
                />
                <img
                    src="/images/jach/11.jpg"
                    alt="JACH visual work"
                    class="w-auto h-60 object-cover"
                />
                <img
                    src="/images/jach/L_Media35.jpg"
                    alt="JACH visual work"
                    class="w-auto h-60 object-cover"
                />
            </div>

            <h3 class="font-bold mt-8 mb-7">Insights</h3>

            <p>
                "We are taught to believe that ambition overrides context. It
                doesn't. Your ecosystem — where you were born, who raised you,
                what city you live in — is not an obstacle to your potential. It
                is the actual boundary of it. Knowing that is not surrender. It
                is the beginning of something real."
            </p>
            <section
                class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center before:content-[''] before:block before:w-[250px] before:border-b-1 before:my-7 before:border-white/50"
            >
            </section>

            <p>
                "For forty thousand generations, pleasure had to earn its place
                through survival. We are only the second or third generation in
                human history that can pursue it freely — and we still don't
                know what to do with it. The guilt you feel about enjoying your
                life is not personal. It is ancient."
            </p>
            <section
                class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center before:content-[''] before:block before:w-[250px] before:border-b-1 before:my-7 before:border-white/50"
            >
            </section>

            <p>
                "Every virtue you pursue carries its opposite inside it. Courage
                without fear is recklessness. Generosity without limits is
                self-destruction. The goal was never to become good. It was to
                stop pretending the other half doesn't exist."
            </p>
            <section
                class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center before:content-[''] before:block before:w-[250px] before:border-b-1 before:my-7 before:border-white/50"
            >
            </section>

            <p>
                "The problem is not that people think badly. It is that they
                think fast. Simplified identities, binary conclusions, immediate
                certainty — these are not signs of conviction. They are signs of
                a culture that has confused speed with clarity."
            </p>

        </section>
        <section class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center text-[27px] leading-[1.15] mt-5">
            <h3 class="font-bold">This work extends into:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Conferences</li>
                <li>Advisory</li>
                <li>Publications and books</li>
                <li>Selected Collaborations</li>
            </ul>

        </section>
    </section>
</Layout>
